  "response": "Barack Obama served two terms as President of the United States from 2009 to 2017. According to the 22nd Amendment to the U.S. Constitution, a person cannot be elected to the office of the President more than twice. Therefore, Barack Obama was not eligible to run for president again in the 2016 election. The 2016 election took place, and the candidates were Hillary Clinton and Donald Trump, with Trump winning the presidency. Thus, there were zero chances of Barack Obama becoming president again in the 2016 election.",
